<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38167f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38167f">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38167f"> 167(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> My heart of my / mother</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Since the heart was considered to be the seat of all will, emotion, feeling, reason and intelligence, Ani&apos;s heart <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> is seen in one pan of the Balance, and in the other is the feather <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> symbolic of truth and righteousness. Whilst his heart was in the Balance Ani, repeating the words of Chapter XXXB of the Book of the Dead, addressed it, saying, &ldquo;<mark>My heart of my mother!</mark> My heart of my mother! My heart of my being! Make no stand against me when testifying, thrust me not back before the Tchatchaut (i.e., the overseers of Osiris), and make no failure in respect of me before the Master of the Balance. <small> E.A. Wallis Budge, <a name="BOD2" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BOD2"><cite title="source">The Book of the Dead</cite></a> (1920) 27-8</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c08019j" href="c08all.htm#c08019j">VI.C.08:019(j)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
